The paper focuses on the use of simulators in robotics, specifically for manipulation-oriented tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve simulation accuracy, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of a motion capture system and the analysis of quantitative data suggest that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as these fields are often used in conjunction with robotics research.
